[I] Let's Encrypt is a new Certificate Authority

[T] Let's Encrypt is a free, automated, and open certificate authority (CA),
[T] run for the public's benefit. Let's Encrypt is a service provided by the
[T] Internet Security Research Group (ISRG).

[U] https://letsencrypt.org

[A] Internet Security Research Group
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/security

[E] add acme
[E] add parsedatetime
[E] add python-configobj
[E] add python-cryptography
[E] add python-josepy
[E] add pyrequests
[E] add pyidna
[E] add python-pyopenssl
[E] add pyrfc3339
[E] add python-configargparse
[E] add pydistro

[L] APL
[V] 5.4.0

[D] f55d03c3c3f85d7a371c3fe03d02b7b9160177ad0b6030e99ba8ff1d certbot-5.4.0.tar.gz https://github.com/certbot/certbot/archive/v5.4.0/

runmake=0
hook_add preconf 5 "cd $pkg"
